# ====================================
# PropGroup Monorepo Environment Variables
# ====================================
# This is the ROOT .env.example file for the monorepo

# ====================================
# DEPLOYMENT ARCHITECTURE
# ====================================
# Deployment: Docker on Coolify (Hetzner)
# Database: PostgreSQL (Coolify managed or external)
# Both Frontend (Next.js) and Backend (Express) run in Docker containers

# ====================================
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLE LOCATIONS
# ====================================
# Each app has its own .env.example with detailed instructions:
#
# Backend:
#   → apps/backend/.env.example
#
# Frontend:
#   → apps/web/.env.example
#
# For local development:
#   → apps/web/.env.local (create from apps/web/.env.example)
#   → apps/backend/.env (create from apps/backend/.env.example)

# ====================================
# QUICK START FOR LOCAL DEVELOPMENT
# ====================================
# 1. Set up backend:
#    cd apps/backend
#    cp .env.example .env
#    # Edit .env with your local PostgreSQL credentials
#
# 2. Set up frontend:
#    cd apps/web
#    cp .env.example .env.local
#    # Set NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3001/api
#
# 3. Install dependencies:
#    pnpm install
#
# 4. Run database migrations:
#    cd packages/db
#    pnpm run db:migrate
#
# 5. Start development servers:
#    pnpm run dev

# ====================================
# FOR PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT
# ====================================
# Set all required variables in your host's environment panel
# (Coolify, Render, Vercel, etc.). Required vars are validated on
# backend boot — see apps/backend/src/utils/validate-env.ts.
